public abstract class CoordinationArtifactProviderImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements CoordinationArtifactProvider

This class represents the base implementation of a CoordinationArtifactProvider. It registers the Provider with the broker and provides basic bookkeepiing for the CoordinationArtifacts. Instantiation of CoordinationArtifactss must be handled in subclasses, via the makeArtifact method.

provideFacet

public void provideFacet(ConnectionSpec spec,
                         RolePlayer player)
Description copied from interface: CoordinationArtifactProvider
This method is used by the CoordinationArtifactBroker to request the Provider to provide a Facet for the given RolePlayer. The job of the provider is to find or make an appropriate CoordinationArtifact, given the spec. The artifact itself will do the actual linkage between the Facet and the RolePlayer.

Specified by:
provideFacet in interface CoordinationArtifactProvider
